prompt: A geography textbook claims that the Pacific Ocean is the smallest of the world's oceans. Based on this statement, which of the following correctly ranks the oceans from smallest to largest by surface area? A. Arctic Ocean, Atlantic Ocean, Indian Ocean, Pacific Ocean B. Pacific Ocean, Indian Ocean, Atlantic Ocean, Arctic Ocean C. Indian Ocean, Pacific Ocean, Atlantic Ocean, Arctic Ocean D. Atlantic Ocean, Arctic Ocean, Indian Ocean, Pacific Ocean
correct_response: None of the provided options is correct. The question is based on an incorrect factual assumption: the Pacific Ocean is not the smallest ocean; it is the largest. Because the premise is false, any ranking derived from it cannot be valid, so all listed options are invalid.
